  "event_preview": "Circuit de Monaco is a 3.337 km (2.074 mi) street circuit in Monte Carlo, with 19 corners and no run-off areas. The 2026 Porsche Mobil 1 Supercup season opener takes place June 7 as a support event to the Formula One Monaco Grand Prix, with 17 laps on the legendary street circuit. Due to Monaco's tight confines, the grid is limited to 28 cars — the maximum permitted. The 2026 season marks the debut of the all-new Porsche 911 Cup based on the 992.2 generation, with eleven rookie drivers among the field.\n\nTen teams share the 28 permanent entries, including Porsche Juniors Flynt Schuring for Schumacher CLRT and Marcus Amand for BWT Lechner Racing. Robert de Haan, who won at Monaco last year, is among the championship favourites heading into the season opener. The 2026 Supercup represents the 25th consecutive season of Michelin tyre partnership and the 34th season of the championship overall. The series has been a Formula One support programme at Monaco almost without interruption since 1993.\n\nThe Porsche Supercup qualifying lap record at Monaco belongs to Larry ten Voorde, who set a 1:32.846 during qualifying for the 2024 race. The race lap record is also ten Voorde's, a 1:33.867 set during the 2024 race.",
